Project: QuantVault - Portfolio Analytics Dashboard
Stack: Python Flask backend, vanilla HTML/JS/CSS frontend
Database: PostgreSQL via SQLAlchemy
External API: Alpha Vantage for stock prices

Structure:
- backend/main.py (Flask app entry point)
- backend/models.py (SQLAlchemy models)
- backend/routes/ (API route handlers)
- backend/services/ (business logic, API calls)
- frontend/index.html (single page app)
- requirements.txt (Python dependencies)

Rules:
- Always use SQLAlchemy ORM, never raw SQL
- Frontend uses fetch() to call backend API endpoints
- All API responses should be JSON
- Use existing code style and patterns
- Do not hardcode any API keys or database URLs
- Do not modify .gitignore or .env
- Keep all frontend code in the single index.html file